2. AI TRANSPARENCY LABEL SYSTEM (Creative Commons BY-SA 4.0)
═════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

The AI Transparency Label taxonomy — including the composable
stage-based labelling framework (AI-0, AI-R, AI-RO, AI-RD, AI-RP,
AI-IRODP, and all combinations) built on the five-stage model
(Idea · Research · Organise · Draft · Polish) — is licensed under
the Creative Commons Attribution-ShareAlike 4.0 International License.

You are free to:

  Share — copy and redistribute the label system in any medium or format
  Adapt — remix, transform, and build upon the label system for any
          purpose, including commercial use

Under the following terms:

  Attribution — You must give appropriate credit, provide a link to
                the licence, and indicate if changes were made.
  ShareAlike  — If you remix, transform, or build upon the label system,
                you must distribute your contributions under the same
                or a compatible licence.

This means you may implement the AI Transparency Label system in your
own tools, newsroom policies, editorial guidelines, and publications,
provided you credit the original work and share adaptations under
compatible terms.

